narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if it is offered again.

If you have any interest in studying the life of Gandhi, I would recommend it. It is a fun and engaging course. You'll challenge your thinking in many broader strokes by examining Gandhi's philosophy and lifestyle.This was a enjoyable course which gave enjoyable assignments.

In Summary! -- EVERYTHING YOU EVER WANTED TO KNOW ABOUT GANDHI!!This class takes you into philosophy, history, political theory and so much more. Prof Desai is ammazing! but be careful, if you dive too deeply into gandhian philosophy is might make you slightly crazy... If the point of education is to change the way, or as some might say "enhance" the way you look at the world this class definitely does that!
Yes. It's a great class and wonderful opporunity to learn something interesting and valuable.
Take it! You learn a lot about a really important historical figure with a great professor.
Take this class even if you have no real interest in Gandhi or Indian historyyou won't regret it.
